 While this strategy proved effective when developmental growth was high during the first Berjaya administration (1976-81), the relative collapse of the state economy from 1982 onwards exposed its ethnic predilections and prefigured declining support for the regime, particularly among the non-Muslim bumiputera groups. Despite the consolidation of federal support for Berjaya under the Mahathir administration, the unravelling of the Berjaya project was by this stage unstoppable. In the final analysis, the attempt to create a more compliant state administration under Berjaya came undone precisely because it failed to take into account the localized dimension of politics in Sabah.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 7aHISTORY / Asia / Southeast Asia.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102470708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066300608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z97831106066830 cprintz978981230812240uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981230813940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789812308139423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789812308139/original  a978-3-11-060668-3  ISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  a978-3-11-066300-6  ISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-102470-7  ISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles 